A woman was found brutally stabbed to death in a robbery, while walking home from work on Tuesday evening, 21 July. KZN Emergency Medical Services was called by pedestrians, when they found the woman in a pool of blood along the pavement on Lyell Street. It is alleged that the woman was being robbed, when she was stabbed several times by her attacker. The unknown suspect fled on foot.  The woman was declared dead on the scene. The woman has not yet been officially identified. Ladysmith Police will be investigating a case of murder. Police are appealing for any information that might assist them in their investigation. The police can be contacted at the toll-free number 08600 10111 or at ‘MySAPS’App to provide information. The nearest police station can also be contacted.